<p>Kim Laughton is a digital artist and designer whose work spans music, fashion, and virtual worlds. Based in Shanghai, he is known for creating uncanny digital environments that blur the boundaries between the synthetic and the real. His practice incorporates 3D modeling, game engines, and video to craft surreal visual experiences often situated within club culture and online communities. Laughton has collaborated with musicians, labels, and fashion designers internationally, while also developing personal projects that probe the aesthetics of simulation, desire, and the shifting textures of digital life.</p>

